Node Name       CAN ID  BLE ID  Description
BP35            0x40	  0x10	  Power Management Unit (PMU). Controls physical relays (Pumps, Lights), manages battery charging, and reports voltage.
DCX	            0x40    0x12	  Power Management Unit (PMU). Controls physical relays (Pumps, Lights), and reports voltage. (NO 240V)
J35	            0x40	  0x14	  Power Management Unit (PMU). Controls physical relays (Pumps, Lights), manages battery charging, and reports voltage.
Voltage Sensor	0x62    0x10    Main Battery Voltage (e.g., 12.6V)
Current Sensor	0x61    0x10		Amps In/Out (e.g., -2.5A)
Capacity Sensor	0x6A    0x10		Ah Remaining (e.g., 82Ah)
SoC Sensor	    0x66    0x10		State of Charge % (e.g., 57%)
Temp Sensor	    0x67    0x10		Battery Temperature
AC Mains	      0x68    0x10		Shore Power Status (On/Off)
Switch Bank	    0x40    0x10		Status of Pumps, Lights, Aux

Battery Voltage	62	Bytes 2 & 3	(Value) / 1000
Battery Amps	61	Bytes 2 & 3	(Value) / 10 (Signed Int)
Water Tank 1	18009083	Byte 4 (Index 01)	((raw - 65) / 185) * 100
Water Tank 2	18009083	Byte 4 (Index 02)	((raw - 65) / 185) * 100
Pump 1 Load	42	Byte 4	00 = Off / >0 = Amps
Pump 2 Load	4D	Byte 4	00 = Off / >0 = Amps
Light Zone 1	49	01	00	1-Byte
Light Zone 2	4A	01	00	1-Byte
Light Zone 3	4B	01	00	1-Byte
Water Pump 1	4C	0100	0000	2-Byte
Water Pump 2	4D	0100	0000	2-Byte

OutputMgr	      16	            The Switchboard. Manages the physical relays (Pumps, Lights). It processes the 3c... commands you send to Registers 110/111 (0x6E/0x6F).
ExtSource	      16	          	Power Monitor. Logic that specifically watches Solar/Aux inputs separate from the main battery.

CN103           0x20    0x24	  System Controller (Gateway).
Tank Sender	    0x83    0x24		Water Levels (1-4)
Slide Out	4E	01	00	Momentary*
Slide In	4F	01	00	Momentary*

TempSensor	    36	        	  Thermometer. (New Finding) A previously unseen capability to read ambient/battery temperature.
Uploader        36	          	OTA Manager. Handles firmware updates for devices on the bus.
Ble2Can	        0x20	  0x28	  Bluetooth Bridge. The interface you connect to. It filters traffic and enforces the "Lockout" state.

Trek2	          0x90	  0x20	  Wall Display. The touch screen unit. It reads telemetry and sends user commands.
RVView	        0x90	  0x2C	  Advanced Monitoring Display.

SmartLink	      0x80	  0x30	  Wireless Hub. Older generic gateway ID.

BC300      	128	    0x80	  Dedicated Battery Monitor / Shunt.
CanAP	      16384	  0x4000	CAN Access Point (Wi-Fi Bridge?).
Generic	    16400	  0x4010	Fallback device type for unknown hardware.
RVView      44      0x2C    Monitor Display. An older style LCD status panel. 
AC Charger  8       0x08    Mains Charger. A standalone 240V charger node (if not built into the BP35).
Solar Reg   4       0x04    MPPT Regulator. Standalone solar controller node.
Inv         12      0x0C    Inverter. 12V to 240V inverter status node. 



